# AGENTS.md

> This file is the cross-agent operating guide for this repository.
> It defines the premium UI standard, forbidden patterns, available skills, and recommended workflows.
> All coding agents working in this repository must follow these rules.

## Premium UI Standard

This repository follows a premium UI standard. All UI work must be:

- Serious, trustworthy, and professional
- System-driven, not ad-hoc or decorative
- Consistent across all screens, components, and states
- Accessible (WCAG 2.2 AA minimum)
- Responsive (mobile-first, all breakpoints considered)
- Aligned with the design system ÔÇö no one-off styling

## Non-Negotiable Principles

- Every component must belong to the design system
- Every screen must follow established layout patterns
- Every interaction must be consistent with existing patterns
- Typography, spacing, and color must come from the token system
- Accessibility is not optional ÔÇö it is a baseline requirement
- Responsive behavior must be defined, not assumed

## Forbidden Visual Patterns

Do not use any of the following:

- Emojis (unless explicitly justified by product requirements)
- Sparkle icons, magic motifs, or AI gimmick visuals
- Robot-head, glowing-brain, or floating-orb AI clich├ęs
- Childish illustrations or sticker-like iconography
- Decorative gradients without design-system purpose
- Excessive glow, blur, or glass effects
- Fake premium through layered effects
- Generic startup/SaaS template aesthetics
- Trendy styling without design-system logic

## Available Skills

This repository uses the following 12 skills for premium UI and design-system work:

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `design-system-setup` | Initialize or update repository agent configuration (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md) |
| `design-system-review` | Review an existing design system for quality and completeness |
| `ui-component-design` | Design new reusable UI components with proper states and variants |
| `premium-ui-refinement` | Elevate existing UI to feel more premium and polished |
| `ux-consistency-audit` | Audit cross-screen UX coherence and pattern consistency |
| `screen-composition-design` | Build or restructure full screens with proper layout and hierarchy |
| `token-architecture` | Define or audit scalable token systems (colors, spacing, typography) |
| `component-implementation-spec` | Create implementation-ready engineering handoff specifications |
| `design-critique` | Provide sharp, high-standard critical review of design work |
| `brand-ui-alignment` | Check whether UI expresses the intended brand character |
| `responsive-adaptive-design` | Define responsive strategies, breakpoints, and adaptive behavior |
| `accessibility` | Audit or define accessibility standards (WCAG 2.2 compliance) |

